
/*
 * The code snippet demonstrates the use of the [add] slot to append a new node to a specified location. It adds a node with the name [hl] and a value derived from the expression [x:@.type] as a child to the nodes obtained from the expression [x:@.tmp/*]. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends a new node to the specified location.
 * 2. [hl] - The name of the node being added.
 * 3. [x:@.type] - The expression used to determine the value of the [hl] node.
 */
add:x:@.tmp/*
   .
      hl:x:@.type
